comments[17]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-31T10:09:36.633Z",codex-audit-20260531,"Duplicate check 2026-05-31: ran pm context, pm search for broad audit/sdk/ecosystem/agent UX/telemetry/external packages, pm list-open, and pm list-in-progress. No open or in-progress audit items existed. Reusing canonical package-first lineage pm-59gj; recent related children pm-qmx3 and pm-oxyo are closed, so this item tracks only the new latest-main 2026-05-31 pass."
  "2026-05-31T10:09:51.519Z",codex-audit-20260531,"Audit plan: bootstrap latest main and contracts; dogfood in isolated temp PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH; inspect SDK/package authoring surfaces and external package install/upgrade; review agent low-token outputs and forgiving command contracts; scan docs/CI/dependencies/security/performance/telemetry/Sentry; implement the smallest durable fixes; link files/docs/tests; run local gates, push PR, wait for AI review, address valid feedback, and merge after green checks."
  "2026-05-31T10:22:10.184Z",codex-audit-20260531,"Evidence so far: bootstrapped latest main c5a86254 with npm install -g ., pm --version 2026.5.31, Node v25.9.0, pnpm 10.33.4, and pnpm build. Required pm orientation found no open/in-progress duplicates; created child under pm-59gj. Bundled package-first dogfood passed 84 commands; semantic dogfood passed 86 commands with qwen3-embedding:0.6b. Repo health brief passed; validate history drift passed with only legacy closed-item resolution warnings. External npm package sweep installed 15 official pm-package packages successfully and exposed pm-starter/pm-ts-starter preflight/renderer collisions; patched doctor and health triage to emit package names plus deactivate/policy remediation, with focused tests passing 90/90."
  "2026-05-31T10:37:29.578Z",codex-audit-20260531,"Progress: resumed audit on branch codex/external-package-contract-audit-20260531 after required bootstrap. Continuing existing canonical item, spawning specialist read-only sub-agents for SDK/package, agent UX/contracts, CI/security/telemetry, and code quality/performance review."
  "2026-05-31T10:37:46.517Z",sdk-package-review-20260531,"Starting read-only SDK/package ecosystem review: checking public SDK/package authoring docs, runtime contract surfaces, package/extension command ergonomics, and lifecycle stability. No file edits or item creation by this sub-agent."
  "2026-05-31T10:37:50.403Z",ci-security-telemetry-review-20260531,"Review start: read-only CI/security/telemetry pass for workflows, dependency scripts, secret hygiene, Sentry gate, and safe telemetry validation surfaces. No file edits, item creation, claims, or reversions will be made."
  "2026-05-31T10:37:54.789Z",code-quality-performance-review-20260531,"Start read-only code quality/performance review: scope is static inspection plus non-mutating checks only; no file edits, no pm item creation, no reverts."
  "2026-05-31T10:37:55.002Z",agent-ux-contract-review-20260531,"Start read-only agent/token-efficient UX contract review: inspecting contracts/help/default output/error guidance only; no file edits, item creation, or reverts."
  "2026-05-31T10:41:20.665Z",ci-security-telemetry-review-20260531,"Final ci-security-telemetry-review: read-only pass completed. Findings: High - tracked sentry-telemetry gate calls ignored/local-only telemetry script, so required telemetry is not reproducible in a clean checkout; Medium - release gates can skip Sentry when secrets are absent and allow nonzero fatal/error thresholds with telemetry off/best-effort; Medium - workflows restore shared ~/.cache/sentry-cli cache in PR-visible jobs, increasing observability data/credential-cache risk; Low - Sentry CLI fallback uses a non-package 'sentry' binary while devDependency exposes sentry-cli. Verified: node scripts/check-secrets.mjs passed, pnpm audit --audit-level moderate passed, local Sentry/telemetry gate passed with available local credentials. Unverified: clean CI required-telemetry execution and current GitHub Actions run state."
  "2026-05-31T10:42:04.214Z",code-quality-performance-review-20260531,"Final code-quality/performance review findings: Medium: src/cli/commands/extension/doctor.ts:166-172 parses colon-delimited collision warnings by fixed indexes, but command/parser names are free-form and may contain colons; warning producers in src/core/extensions/loader.ts:1907 and :1966 place command before layer/name fields, so a command like acme:sync yields Conflicting extensions: project instead of package names. Fix by parsing collision warning fields from the right or emitting structured collision diagnostics, and add colon-in-command regression coverage. Low: src/cli/commands/extension/doctor.ts:150-196 groups extension_command_override_handler_overlap with later-registration collisions even though loader emits only extension_command_override_handler_overlap:<command> at src/core/extensions/loader.ts:1921; docs/SDK.md:165 says collision warnings include package names, but this case cannot. Either enrich the overlap warning with handler/override extension names or use a separate remediation that does not promise names/later-wins semantics. Checks: git diff --check passed; pnpm exec tsc --noEmit --incremental false -p tsconfig.json passed; pnpm exec tsc --noEmit --incremental false -p tsconfig.packages.json passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts tests/unit/health-command.spec.ts passed 90/90. Note: the test wrapper invoked build before tests."
  "2026-05-31T10:42:56.589Z",sdk-package-review-20260531,"Final sdk-package-review findings (read-only):\n\n1. HIGH - Default `pm package init` scaffold can produce a package that fails after install because its generated nested extension imports `@unbrained/pm-cli/sdk` at runtime while only declaring a package-root peerDependency. The scaffold writes `pm.extensions: [\"extensions/<name>\"]`, `peerDependencies: { \"@unbrained/pm-cli\": \"*\" }`, and `extensions/<name>/index.js` with a bare SDK import (src/cli/commands/extension/scaffold.ts:50-145). Install resolves/copies only the concrete extension directory (src/core/packages/manifest.ts:249-281; src/cli/commands/extension/install-sources.ts:378-445; src/cli/commands/extension.ts:1071-1084). Local installs do not install dependencies, and npm installs deps at package root before copying, so nested extensions can lose package-root node_modules. Recommended fix: make the generated package use a root extension (`pm.extensions: [\".\"]`) or make the generated command import-free like extension-only scaffold; add an end-to-end test for `pm package init ./pkg` -> `pm install ./pkg --project` -> generated command executes in an isolated project.\n\n2. MEDIUM - Runtime contracts do not address nested package lifecycle subcommands even though docs tell agents to use contracts for exact flags. `pm contracts --command package --flags-only --json` works but only returns top-level lifecycle flags; `pm contracts --command 'package init' --flags-only --json`, `'package install'`, and `'package catalog'` return Unknown command. `pm package catalog --help --json` exposes subcommand-only `--fields`, so contracts and help diverge. Refs: docs/COMMANDS.md:3-9, src/sdk/cli-contracts/enum-contracts.ts:28-81, src/cli/commands/contracts.ts:1533-1564, src/cli/register-setup.ts:204-290. Recommended fix: add first-class contract keys for nested lifecycle commands or make `--command` resolve Commander paths and include subcommand flags.\n\n3. LOW - Machine-readable help for package/extension subcommands falls back to root narrative. `pm package init --help --json`, `pm package install --help --json`, and `pm package catalog --help --json` report intent \"Provides deterministic project management workflows...\" and examples `[\"pm init\"]`, which is actively misleading for package authors. Refs: src/cli/help-content.ts:101-173 and 643-659, src/cli/help-json-payload.ts:238-294. Recommended fix: add `HELP_BY_COMMAND_PATH` entries for package/extension subcommands or nearest-ancestor fallback plus regression coverage.\n\nNo file edits were made intentionally. Unexpected side effect observed: package inspection changed only `.agents/pm/extensions/.managed-extensions.json` updated_at from 2026-05-31T09:47:41.573Z to 2026-05-31T10:38:38.115Z; not reverted per instructions. I did not run scaffold/install dogfood because this sub-agent was instructed to stay read-only.\n\nKey commands run: pm --version; node -v; pnpm -v; git status --short; pm package --help --json; pm package init/install/catalog --help --json; pm contracts --command package/extension/install --flags-only --json; pm contracts --command 'package init'/'package install'/'package catalog' --flags-only --json; pm contracts --runtime-only --availability-only --json; pm package explore/manage/doctor/catalog --project --json; rg/sed/nl reads over docs/SDK.md, docs/EXTENSIONS.md, src/sdk*, src/cli/commands/extension*, src/core/packages*, contracts/help, and relevant tests.\n"
  "2026-05-31T10:42:59.598Z",codex-audit-20260531,"Sub-agent findings integrated: CI/security review flagged private telemetry gate coupling and Sentry cache/fallback concerns; code-quality review found the new collision parser used fixed colon indexes and over-promised package names for command override/handler overlap warnings. Both are being treated as actionable fixes before PR."
  "2026-05-31T10:44:01.656Z",codex-audit-20260531,"Cleanup: agent-UX sub-agent accidentally created placeholder items pm-crpv, pm-lql3, and pm-11ag while probing command behavior. Closed all three through pm as invalid accidental sub-agent probe items; canonical audit item remains pm-kd9n."
  "2026-05-31T10:46:39.575Z",agent-ux-contract-review-20260531,"Final agent-ux-contract-review: read-only review completed aside from requested pm comments. Side effect: typo probes for create unexpectedly created pm-crpv/pm-lql3/pm-11ag because bootstrap typo-normalization silently rewrites misspelled mutating flags; lead cleanup closed them as invalid. Findings: High - src/cli/bootstrap-args.ts:432-480,502-528,679-735 plus tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts:218-228 silently autocorrect create flag typos such as --titel/--titl to --title and writes items with no warning; make typo rewrites advisory/visible for mutating commands, or require explicit retry/acceptance and include normalization_events in output/history. High - src/cli/commands/contracts.ts:318-359,1533-1564,1648-1754 and src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts:1122-1230 advertise action command_path values like package install/extension doctor but pm contracts --command \"package install\" --flags-only --json rejects them; accept advertised command paths/action names and return subcommand-specific flags. Medium - pm contracts --command calendar --availability-only --runtime-only --json exits 2 instead of a nonblocking availability=false optional-package record; synthesize package availability with install_command for availability-only. Medium - pm calendar --help text emits full root help before unknown-command guidance; intercept unknown help paths before commander writes root help. Medium - pm get default is deep/unbounded and duplicates linked metadata (src/cli/commands/get.ts:82-99,225-239; src/cli/register-list-query.ts:277-281); default to brief/standard and require --full for comments/body/deep links. Medium - invalid-value retry examples can rewrite the wrong flag because provided fields are sorted (src/cli/argv-utils.ts:17-26, src/cli/error-guidance.ts:285-299); pm list --sort upd --limit 1 suggests --limit priority. Commands sampled include context/list/get/search/health/package/extension help, contracts flags/schema/availability, optional command help, and invalid option/value paths."
  "2026-05-31T11:17:33.963Z",codex-audit-20260531,"Evidence update 2026-05-31 final local gates: pnpm build passed; pnpm typecheck passed; focused regression suite passed 175/175; coverage passed 135 files and 2063/2063 tests with 100 percent instrumented coverage; bundled package-first dogfood passed 87 commands including generated package scaffold install/run; semantic dogfood passed 89 commands with qwen3-embedding:0.6b; check-secrets passed; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate found no vulnerabilities; docs-skills gate passed; static-quality gate passed; git diff --check passed; pm health --check-only --brief --json ok with telemetry queue healthy and recent flush; pm validate history drift ok with only 29 pre-existing closed-item resolution warnings; Sentry/telemetry gate passed with zero critical/high Sentry issues and required telemetry finish error rate 1.29 percent; telemetry stack health showed all core services healthy, queue depth 0, and 7407 events in the last 24h. External npm registry sweep after final build found 15 first-party pm-package packages and installed all 15 in an initialized temp project with failed=0; package doctor reported only pm-starter/pm-ts-starter preflight and json renderer single-winner collisions with the new package-named remediation."
  "2026-05-31T11:39:55.395Z",codex-audit-20260531,"PR review response: addressed Gemini and Sourcery suggestions by table-driving core command flag contract lookup, centralizing registration collision warning parsing, adding y-to-ies list alias candidate handling with coverage, defensively formatting typo trace events, and allowing telemetry query commands to execute directly unless they are .sh scripts. Addressed CodeRabbit valid findings by switching Sentry fallback to the modern sentry issue list executable and canceling accidental probe items so changelog generation ignores invalid tracker noise. Skipped CodeRabbit's .agents/pm removal suggestion because these tracker files were produced through pm commands, not direct edits, and are required project-management evidence for this audit."
  "2026-05-31T18:29:39.767Z",codex-pr-review-followup,"Evidence: addressed latest PR review feedback after commit 94152f83. Fixes include required telemetry missing-command failure, explicit retry recovery preservation, mutating operation typo guards for claim/release/start/pause/close/test, subcommand-aware package catalog list-flag coalescing, package/packages lifecycle contract aliases, optional package action availability for direct --action calendar, root templates/test-runs command-to-action mapping, and truncated plural flags staying in the typo path. Verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/bootstrap-args.spec.ts tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/release-automation-contract.spec.ts (127/127); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (135 files, 2068/2068 tests, 100% coverage); git diff --check; node scripts/check-secrets.mjs; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift ok with only 29 pre-existing closed-item resolution warnings and history drift ok."
